==I - Prime==
{{Phenomenon Class|frequency=1|effectiveness=4|danger=1}}
{{Blurimage|file=20201031 150307.jpg|caption=One of [[Level 9]]'s safe places.}}
Phenomenon 18, informally known as "Safe Places" manifest in open areas that have some sort of danger, ''hazards or entities''<ref>Safe Places normally manifest within dangerous levels; But also safe levels.</ref>. In regards to rarity, Safe Places are incredibly infrequent; with there being 3 in a level at most. The Phenomenon has gained a near-mythical status among wanderers. A Safe Place usually manifests as a shady, tree-lined road which averages at 10-15 metres across, surrounded by dusty pavement. The centre of the area lies a lamppost, around 4 metres tall; with a yellow sign reading "A SAFE PLACE".

Around the lamppost is a ''invisible, electromagnetic field''<ref>An invisible, electromagnetic field is present around the lamppost.</ref>, Entities that enter this radius will be repelled, which includes normally friendly entities like [[Facelings]] and [[Glowfolk]] will be pushed back too. Reports claim that harsh environments from other levels like [[Level 99]] or [[Level 123]] will be weakened; But this has not been confirmed yet.
==II - Appearances==
Safe Places have been noted to appear in open areas with variable forms of danger; specific level appearances include:
*[[Level 123]]
*[[Level 24]]
*[[Level 99]]
*[[Level 9]]
*[[Level 995]]
*[[Level 37]]
*[[Level 11]]
*[[Level 12]]
*[[Level 999]]
*[[Level 525]]
*[[Level 4]]
*[[Level 588]]
==III - The Cycle==
{{Blurimage|file=Veil.jpg|caption=A manifestation of Phenomenon 18, showcasing two lampposts instead of one.}}
Safe Places will operate on a 12-hour clock cycle, know as simply "The Cycle" or "Safe Place Time". This event warps space around the lamppost in the middle of the area, eventually making the space collapse upon itself and turn into nothing. This is also a sign of what could be known as ''False Safe Places''<ref>False Safe places are variants of the latter, but with danger instead of safety; earning it's name.</ref>.
==IV - False Safe Places==
In the aftermath of The First Euphoric War, a group of infected Partygoers erected fake safe place signs within levels like [[Level Fun]] & [[New Fun]]; these false safe places are used to ambush anybody who enters the space. Since that day, various groups have attempted doing this with various means of success. 

Some ways to identify False Safe Places are:
*Not being  surrounded by grass/concrete
*Party decorations
*A slanted lamppost
*An extra lamppost
*Any form of entity.
*The light being unlit or flickering.
*The absence of a lamppost.
